tasks.description:
Replace the broken OR logic for Pulse initialization in `apps/server/src/index.ts` with the `'KEY' in process.env` pattern.

The current code at line 102 uses OR logic that cannot honor an explicit `DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED=false` because `boolFlag` in `env.ts` defaults to `false` when the env var is absent — `env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED || schedulerConfig.enabled` always resolves to `true` (config default wins).

**File:** `apps/server/src/index.ts`

**Exact change (lines 100–103):**

BEFORE:
```typescript
// Initialize Pulse scheduler if enabled
const schedulerConfig = configManager.get('scheduler');
const pulseEnabled = env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED || schedulerConfig.enabled;
```

AFTER:
```typescript
// Initialize Pulse scheduler if enabled
const schedulerConfig = configManager.get('scheduler');
// Env var wins when explicitly set; fall back to config when not set.
// boolFlag defaults to false even when unset, so check process.env directly.
// eslint-disable-next-line no-restricted-syntax -- checks key existence (not value); env.ts boolFlag can't distinguish "unset" from "set to false"
const pulseEnabled =
  'DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED' in process.env ? env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED : schedulerConfig.enabled;
```

The `eslint-disable-next-line` comment is required and must match the exact pattern already used in the Relay block (line 121) — the same reasoning applies. `schedulerConfig` is always a validated object from the Zod config schema with `enabled: true` as default, so no optional chaining is needed.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- `'DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED' in process.env` pattern is used (not `env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED ||`)
- `eslint-disable-next-line no-restricted-syntax` comment with explanation is present
- `schedulerConfig.enabled` (no `?.`) is used as the fallback
- `pnpm typecheck` passes
- `pnpm lint` passes

Remove the `?? false` fallback from Relay initialization in `apps/server/src/index.ts` and update the comment block above it.

The current code at line 125 has `relayConfig?.enabled ?? false` — the `?? false` overrides the config schema default of `true` on fresh installs (where `relayConfig.enabled` is `true` from the Zod schema). The optional chaining `?.` is also unnecessary since `configManager.get('relay')` always returns a validated object.

**File:** `apps/server/src/index.ts`

**Exact change (lines 117–130):**

BEFORE:
```typescript
  // Initialize Relay if enabled
  const relayConfig = configManager.get('relay');
  // Env var wins when explicitly set; fall back to config when not set.
  // boolFlag defaults to false even when unset, so check process.env directly.
  // eslint-disable-next-line no-restricted-syntax -- checks key existence (not value); env.ts boolFlag can't distinguish "unset" from "set to false"
  const relayEnabled =
    'DORKOS_RELAY_ENABLED' in process.env
      ? env.DORKOS_RELAY_ENABLED
      : (relayConfig?.enabled ?? false);

  // Phase A: core relay infrastructure (RelayCore + TraceStore)
  // AdapterManager construction is deferred to Phase C (after meshCore init)
  // so that meshCore is available for CWD resolution via buildContext().
  const relayDataDir = relayConfig?.dataDir ?? path.join(dorkHome, 'relay');
```

AFTER:
```typescript
  // Initialize Relay if enabled
  const relayConfig = configManager.get('relay');
  // Env var wins when explicitly set; fall back to config when not set.
  // boolFlag defaults to false even when unset, so check process.env directly.
  // eslint-disable-next-line no-restricted-syntax -- checks key existence (not value); env.ts boolFlag can't distinguish "unset" from "set to false"
  const relayEnabled =
    'DORKOS_RELAY_ENABLED' in process.env ? env.DORKOS_RELAY_ENABLED : relayConfig.enabled;

  // Phase A: core relay infrastructure (RelayCore + TraceStore)
  // AdapterManager construction is deferred to Phase C (after meshCore init)
  // so that meshCore is available for CWD resolution via buildContext().
  const relayDataDir = relayConfig.dataDir ?? path.join(dorkHome, 'relay');
```

Two changes on the `relayEnabled` line: remove `?? false` and remove `?.` optional chaining. One additional change: `relayConfig?.dataDir` on the `relayDataDir` line also has unnecessary optional chaining — remove `?.` there too for consistency (same reasoning: `configManager.get('relay')` always returns a defined object).

**Acceptance criteria:**
- `relayConfig?.enabled ?? false` is replaced with `relayConfig.enabled` (no `?.`, no `?? false`)
- `relayConfig?.dataDir` is replaced with `relayConfig.dataDir`
- The comment block above the `relayEnabled` declaration is intact and unmodified
- `pnpm typecheck` passes
- `pnpm lint` passes

Add a symmetric Relay config-propagation block to `packages/cli/src/cli.ts` immediately after the existing Pulse block (lines 188–193).

The CLI currently propagates the `--pulse`/`--no-pulse` flag and config value into `DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED`. Relay has no equivalent block, creating an asymmetry. There are no `--relay`/`--no-relay` CLI flags (confirmed: not in `parseArgs` options), so the Relay block only propagates from config.

**File:** `packages/cli/src/cli.ts`

**Exact change — insert after line 193 (after the closing `}` of the Pulse block):**

BEFORE (lines 188–195):
```typescript
// Pulse scheduler: CLI flag > env var > config
if (values.pulse !== undefined) {
  process.env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED = values.pulse ? 'true' : 'false';
} else if (!process.env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED && cfgMgr.getDot('scheduler.enabled')) {
  process.env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED = 'true';
}

// Working directory: CLI flag > env var > config > cwd
```

AFTER (lines 188–198):
```typescript
// Pulse scheduler: CLI flag > env var > config
if (values.pulse !== undefined) {
  process.env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED = values.pulse ? 'true' : 'false';
} else if (!process.env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED && cfgMgr.getDot('scheduler.enabled')) {
  process.env.DORKOS_PULSE_ENABLED = 'true';
}

// Relay: env var > config (no CLI flag for relay)
if (!process.env.DORKOS_RELAY_ENABLED && cfgMgr.getDot('relay.enabled')) {
  process.env.DORKOS_RELAY_ENABLED = 'true';
}

// Working directory: CLI flag > env var > config > cwd
```

The `if (!process.env.DORKOS_RELAY_ENABLED ...)` guard ensures the block never overwrites an explicit user-supplied env var, preserving the `DORKOS_RELAY_ENABLED=false` escape hatch. Only sets the env var when absent and the config value is truthy.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- Block is inserted between the Pulse block and the Working directory comment
- Comment reads `// Relay: env var > config (no CLI flag for relay)`
- Only sets `DORKOS_RELAY_ENABLED` when it is not already set in the environment
- Uses `cfgMgr.getDot('relay.enabled')` (matches the pattern `cfgMgr.getDot('scheduler.enabled')` used in the Pulse block)
- `pnpm typecheck` passes
- `pnpm lint` passes
